 BARBERTON – Last week Tuesday was a turning point in the lives of the Barberton Mines bursary recipients’ lives. Past, present and future graduates were honoured at a ceremony which was held at the Diggers Retreat Hotel and hosted by the mine. ALSO READ: WATCH:The fight to attain justice for victims of mine collapse is on A number of local roleplayers were in attendance to celebrate the beneficiaries who will be pursuing careers in mining related fields. Since its inception in 2017, the graduate programme has made it possible for more than 15 graduates from Barberton to enroll at university and follow careers in mining. ALSO READ: SASSA Mbombela service office moves into new premises in town This year’s intake were encouraged to continue working hard at their studies before leaving for university.